'''Shamo Quaye''' ([[October 22]], [[1971]] - [[November 30]], [[1997]]) was a [[football (soccer)|football]] player from [[Ghana]], who was a member of the [[Ghana national football team|Men's National Team]] that won the bronze medal at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona, Spain]].

He played for [[Hearts of Oak]] in his native country and died of a heart attack, while training with his Swedish team [[Ume<U+00E5> FC]].

